# Using yt-dlp on macOS, Windows, and Linux

yt-dlp is a powerful command-line tool for downloading videos from
YouTube and many other platforms. Below is a complete guide to
installing and using yt-dlp on macOS, Windows, and Linux, including how
to play videos directly in the terminal or a media player.

## 1. macOS

\*\*Installation using Homebrew:\*\*

1\. Install Homebrew (if not already installed):

/bin/bash -c \"\$(curl -fsSL
https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)\"

2\. Install yt-dlp:

brew install yt-dlp

3\. Verify installation:

yt-dlp \--version

4\. Optional -- install mpv for video playback:

brew install mpv

You can now stream videos directly without saving them:

mpv \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID\"

## 2. Windows

\*\*Installation using Winget:\*\*

1\. Open Command Prompt or PowerShell.

2\. Install yt-dlp:

winget install yt-dlp

3\. Verify installation:

yt-dlp \--version

Optional -- install mpv for playback:

winget install mpv

Now you can stream videos directly:

mpv \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID\"

## 3. Linux

\*\*Installation using pip:\*\*

1\. Update package manager:

sudo apt update \# For Debian/Ubuntu

2\. Install yt-dlp:

sudo apt install yt-dlp

Alternatively, install via pip:

pip install -U yt-dlp

3\. Verify installation:

yt-dlp \--version

Optional -- install mpv for playback:

sudo apt install mpv

Now you can stream videos directly:

mpv \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID\"

## 4. Usage Examples

\*\*Download a video:\*\*

yt-dlp \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID\"

\*\*Save to a specific folder:\*\*

yt-dlp -o \"\~/Downloads/%(title)s.%(ext)s\"
\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID\"

\*\*Stream without saving (requires mpv):\*\*

mpv \"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=VIDEO_ID\"

\*\*Play a downloaded file (handle special characters):\*\*

mpv \"filename_with\_\[brackets\].webm\"

## 5. Supported Platforms

yt-dlp supports downloading videos and audio from hundreds of websites.
Here are some popular supported platforms:

\- Social Media: Facebook, Instagram, Twitter/X, TikTok, Reddit\
- Streaming Sites: Vimeo, Dailymotion, Bilibili\
- Music Platforms: SoundCloud, Bandcamp\
- News & TV: BBC, CNN, NHK, and more\
- Adult content: Supported (disabled in safe mode)

Note: Some platforms with DRM protection (e.g., Netflix, Amazon Prime,
Disney+, Hotstar) are not supported because bypassing DRM is illegal.

To check if a specific site is supported, run:

yt-dlp \--list-extractors \| grep -i \"site-name\"

Example for TikTok:

yt-dlp \--list-extractors \| grep -i tiktok

For paid or login-required sites, you may need to pass cookies:\
yt-dlp \--cookies cookies.txt \"VIDEO_URL\"
